How to open the downloads directory with MS powertoys
It does not natively allow it, but you can do it with powershell

This is for a computer named front, replace front with your own computer name and path
Here's how it looks Keyboard Manager > Remap a shortcut

ShortCut:  Alt (left)  F12

Action: Run Program
App:c:\windows\system32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe
Args: -Command "& { Start-Process explorer.exe 'C:\Users\front\Downloads' }"
Start in:  empty
ElevationL Normal
if running: show window
Visibility: hidden

Target App:  All apps

Below is how it looks in 
file:///C:/Users/front/AppData/Local/Microsoft/PowerToys/Keyboard%20Manager/default.json
original keys 164;123 = Alt(left) + F12 key

{
        "originalKeys": "164;123",
        "runProgramElevationLevel": 0,
        "secondKeyOfChord": 0,
        "operationType": 1,
        "runProgramAlreadyRunningAction": 0,
        "runProgramStartWindowType": 1,
        "runProgramFilePath": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe",
        "runProgramArgs": "-Command \"& { Start-Process explorer.exe 'C:\\Users\\front\\Downloads' }\"",
        "runProgramStartInDir": "",
        "unicodeText": "*Unsupported*"
      },
